OL,3,CJersey residents support offshore wind
OL,4,Cfarm through public survey
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Jersey's Environment
OL,7,FMinister, Deputy Steve Luce, said: "I
OL,8,Fthink it's really important that we
OL,9,Fcan give a strong signal that we're in
OL,10,Ffavour of moving forward and it's
OL,11,Fsomething we'd like to do.
OL,13,F"We are keen to investigate all the
OL,14,Fproblems, challenges and benefits that
OL,15,Fcould happen from a wind farm
OL,16,Fdevelopment."
OL,18,FAny development is expected to cost
OL,19,Fbillions of pounds of private
OL,20,Finvestment and take around a decade to
OL,21,Fbuild.
